      • resetResolvedEntityRegistrations

        void resetResolvedEntityRegistrations​(RowProcessingState rowProcessingState)
        Resets the resolved entity registrations by i.e. removing EntityHolder. This is used after EntityInitializer.resolveEntityKeyOnly(RowProcessingState) to deregister registrations for entities that were only resolved, but not initialized. Failing to do this will lead to errors, because PersistenceContext.postLoad(JdbcValuesSourceProcessingState, Consumer) is called, which expects all registrations to be fully initialized.
